{{Infobox cycling race report | name = 2009 Vuelta a Venezuela | image = Vuelta Ciclística a Venezuela.jpg | image_size = 350 | image_caption = Peloton at the last stage of the 2009 Vuelta a Venezuela | date = June 24 &ndash; July 5 | series = [[2008–2009 UCI America Tour]] | stages = 12 | distance = 1560.6 | unit = km | time = 39h 09' 51" | speed = 39.8578 | first = [[José Rujano]] | first_nat = VEN | first_team = Gobernacion del Zulía | first_color = red | second = [[César Salazar (cyclist)|César Salazar]] | second_nat = COL | second_team = Loteria del Tachirá | third = [[José Chacón Díaz]] | third_nat = VEN | third_team = G. Carabobo-Tra. Ele | points = [[Honorio Machado]] | points_nat = VEN | points_team = Alcadia Bol.Jimenez | mountains = [[José Rujano]] | mountains_nat = VEN | mountains_team = Gobernacion del Zulía | youth = [[José Alarcón]] | youth_nat = VEN | youth_team = Sumiglov | team = Lotería del Táchira | previous = [[2008 Vuelta a Venezuela|2008]] | next = [[2010 Vuelta a Venezuela|2010]] }}
The 46th edition of the annual '''[[Vuelta a Venezuela]]''' was held from Wednesday June 24 to Sunday July 5, 2009.
