'''The 2017-18 SAFA Second Division''' (known as the ABC Motsepe League for sponsorship reasons) was the 20th season of the [[SAFA Second Division]], the third tier for South African association football clubs, since its establishment in 1998. Due to the size of South Africa, the competition was split into nine divisions, one for each region. After the league stage of the regional competition was completed, the nine wining teams of each regional division entered the playoffs.

It was won by [[Maccabi F.C.]], who beat [[TS Sporting F.C.|TS Sporting]] 5-4 on penalties.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://mysafa.net/2018/06/maccabi-crowned-abc-motsepe-league-champions/ |title=Maccabi crowned ABC Motsepe League champions |last=Mazibuko |first=Thabang |date=9 June 2018 |website=mysafa.net |access-date=2 September 2018}}</ref> Both teams were promoted to the [[2018-19 National First Division]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.safa.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/ABCMOTSEPEPlay-offsProgramme.pdf |title=2018 Motsepe League National Playoffs |website=safa.net |access-date=2018-08-12}}</ref>

