'''[[Fencing]] in the [[Philippines]]''' is governed by the '''[[Philippine Fencing Association]]''' or '''PFA'''. Founded by [[Don Francisco Dayrit Sr.]], PFA is recognized by the [[Philippine Olympic Committee]] (POC) as one of its National Sports Association members and by the [[Federation Internationale d'Escrime]] (FIE), the international governing body for the sport. PFA is also a founding member of the Southeast Asian Fencing Federation (SEAFF) and the Asian Fencing Confederation (AFC). [[Richard Gomez]] is currently the president of PFA while [[Celso Dayrit]] is currently the president of the Fencing Confederation of Asia.
<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philippinefencing.com/ |title=セレブ系の男女が注目している出会い系サイト |publisher=Philippinefencing.com |date= |accessdate=1 February 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120219034723/http://www.philippinefencing.com/ |archivedate=19 February 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.olympic.ph/ |title=Philippine Olympic Committee |publisher=Olympic.ph |date= |accessdate=1 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asianfencing.com/ |title=Asian Fencing Confederation |publisher=Asianfencing.com |date= |accessdate=1 February 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://celsodayrit.com/ |title=Official Website of CELSO DAYRIT |publisher=Celsodayrit.com |date= |accessdate=1 February 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120219034727/http://celsodayrit.com/ |archivedate=19 February 2012 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://sports.inquirer.net/amateur/amateur/view/20090617-211009/Hopes_still_high_for_RP_fencing</ref>

The sport was said to be introduced during the [[Spanish occupation of the Philippines|Spanish colonial era]]. [[Philippine revolution]] personalities such as [[Jose Rizal]], [[Juan Luna]] and Antonio Luna were known to be fencers.

