'''''Gold's Gym: Cardio Workout''''' is an [[exergaming|exercise video game]] for [[Nintendo]]'s [[Wii]] [[video game console]], created by Japanese [[video game developer]] Rocket Company. Based on the "shape boxing" fitness regimen used at Kyoei Boxing Gym<ref name="Kyoei">{{cite web |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2008/09/05/get-in-shape-with-shape-boxing-wii-de-enjoy-diet/ |title=Get in shape with Shape Boxing Wii de Enjoy Diet |first=Spencer |last=Yip |work=Siliconera |date=5 September 2008 |accessdate=10 November 2009 }}</ref> which includes [[shadowboxing]], [[press-up]]s, and [[sit-up (exercise)|sit-up]]s, the game also features a diet management feature. Originally announced in mid-2007 as ''Wii Exercise'' with a release target of later that year,<ref name="Wii Exercise">{{cite web |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2007/08/02/wait-a-second%e2%80%a6-wii-exercise/ |title=Wait a second... Wii Exercise? |first=Spencer |last=Yip |work=Siliconera |date=2 August 2007 |accessdate=4 August 2007}}</ref> in May 2008, the game was stated to still be in an early stage of development. Though not originally intended to feature support for the [[Wii Balance Board]], the feature was announced later.<ref name="BBB">{{cite web |url=http://www.balanceboardblog.com/2008/09/wii-boxing-shape-of-diet-enjoy-balance.html |title=''Shape Boxing: Wii de Enjoy! Diet'' Balance Board use confirmed |first=Andrew |last=Macarthy |work=Balance Board Blog |date=4 September 2008 |accessdate=9 November 2009 |quote= |ref= |separator= |postscript= |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090319092312/http://www.balanceboardblog.com/2008/09/wii-boxing-shape-of-diet-enjoy-balance.html |archivedate=19 March 2009 |df= }}</ref> ''Shape Boxing'' was released in Japan on October 30, 2008 under the title ''Shape Boxing: Wii de Enjoy! Diet'' (シェイプボクシング Wiiでエンジョイダイエット！). The game was licensed by Ubisoft for other regional markets, and released as in Europe as part of the publisher's ''[[My Coach]]'' series as '''''My Fitness Coach: Cardio Workout''''',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mcvuk.com/retail-biz/previews/452/My-Fitness-Coach-Cardio-Workout |title=My Fitness Coach: Cardio Workout exclusive preview |first=James |last=Batchelor |work=MCV |publisher=Intent Media |date=2 July 2009 |accessdate=9 November 2009}}</ref> and released in North America and Australia as ''Gold's Gym: Cardio Workout'',  in partnership with the [[Gold's Gym]] fitness center chain.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=22467 |title=Ubisoft Partners With Gold's Gym For ''Cardio Workout'' |first=Eric |last=Caoili |work=Gamasutra |publisher=Think Services |date=25 February 2009 |accessdate=9 November 2009}}</ref>

