{{Infobox venue
|stadium_name = Palestine Stadium
|location = [[Gaza City]], [[Gaza Strip]]
|tenants = [[Palestine national football team]]
|fullname = Palestine Stadium
|seating_capacity = 10,000
}}
'''Palestine Stadium''' ({{lang-ar|ملعب فلسطين}}) is located in [[Gaza City]] on the [[Gaza Strip]]. It is the national [[stadium]] and the home of [[Palestine national football team]]. The stadium's capacity is around 10,000. 

It was bombed by [[Israel]] on April 1, 2006, directly on the centre spot, and is currently unusable due to the crater formed. [[FIFA]] has announced that it will fund the repair work.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theglobalgame.com/blog/2006/04/field-artillery-bombings-in-kibbutz-and-gaza-represent-new-pitch-invasion/|title=Field artillery - Bombings in kibbutz and Gaza represent new pitch invasion|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-3239176,00.html|title=FIFA to fund Gaza soccer field repair|work=ynet}}</ref> It was again bombed on November 19, 2012, by the [[Israeli Defence Force]] as part of [[Operation Pillar of Cloud]]. Israel claimed that the latest bombing was due to its  use by militants to launch rockets targeting Israel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishpress.com/news/breaking-news/iaf-bombed-the-gaza-stadium-where-missiles-were-fired-from-the-grass/2012/11/19/?src=ataglance|title=IAF Bombed the Gaza Stadium, where Missiles Were Fired from the Grass|author=Jewish Press Staff|work=The Jewish Press}}</ref> 

The stadium and a nearby indoor sports hall suffered major damage and resulted in  notable football players from around the globe releasing a signed petition.<ref>{{cite web|last=Fenn|first=Alec|title=Gaza stadium hit by Israeli air attack|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/14/asia/2012/11/17/3534981/gaza-stadium-hit-by-israeli-air-attack|work=goal.com|accessdate=19 November 2012|date=17 November 2012}}</ref>

