{{infobox country at games | NPC = UGA | NPCname = Uganda National Paralympic Committee | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1972 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Heidelberg]] | competitors = 2 | sports = 1 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Uganda]]''' made its [[Paralympic Games]] début at the '''[[1972 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Heidelberg]], [[West Germany]] - shortly after [[Idi Amin]]'s [[History_of_Uganda#Uganda_under_Amin|rise to power]].
== Background == Uganda made their Paralympic debut at the '''[[1972 Summer Paralympics]]''' in [[Heidelberg]], [[West Germany]]. <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201609290094.html|title=Uganda: Paralympic Medalist, Emong Has Been Driven By Prayer|last=Ssemugabi|first=Abdul Nasser|date=2016-09-29|newspaper=The Monitor (Kampala)|access-date=2016-10-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/rio-2016/uganda|title=Uganda Paralympics - Rio 2016 Medals, Athletes & News|website=www.paralympic.org|access-date=2016-12-25}}</ref>
== Team == Uganda sent a two sportspeople strong delegation to the Games.<ref name=":0">[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=UGA&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Uganda at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paralympic.org/rio-2016/uganda|title=Uganda Paralympics - Rio 2016 Medals, Athletes & News|website=www.paralympic.org|access-date=2016-12-25}}</ref>
== Athletics == {{See also|Athletics at the 1972 Summer Paralympics}} The country entered only two athletes, who both competed in [[athletics at the 1972 Summer Paralympics|men's javelin and shot put]]. Neither of them won a medal.<ref name=":0" />
